<para>\par \b Module Contract\/ \:</para>
<para>\par \b Purpose\/ \:  Define the AttachedFile data structure — holds metadata about files embedded in the parsed document. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>\par \b Scope\/ \:  Attached file metadata storage and access. \par \b Input\/ \:  Original name, temp path, analysis flag, UID. \par \b Output\/ \:  AttachedFile instance. \par \b Links\/ \:  [USED_BY(9): UnstructuredDocument] \par \b Invariants\/ \:</para>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>uid is always a non-empty string</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>original_name may differ from tmp_file_path basename \par \b Rationale\/ \:</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
<para>Q: Why separate original_name from tmp_file_path? A: During processing, files are renamed for uniqueness; the original name is preserved for user presentation. \par \b Changes\/ \:</para>
<para>LAST_CHANGE: [v1.0.0 – Added semantic markup and LDD logging] \par \b Module Map\/ \:</para>
